OL,6,FHollis, who is also a Nottinghamshire
OL,7,Fcounty councillor, pleaded guilty on
OL,8,FMonday to two offences under the
OL,9,FLocalism Act of failing without
OL,10,Freasonable excuse to notify both
OL,11,Fauthorities of a disclosable pecuniary
OL,12,Finterest when he was re-elected in
OL,13,F2019 and 2021.
OL,15,FNottingham Magistrates' Court was told
OL,16,FHollis, of the Ashfield Independents
OL,17,Fgroup, earns #4,500 per month from his
OL,18,Fcouncil roles and loaned around
OL,19,F#70,000 to fellow councillor Helen-Ann
OL,20,FSmith in 2018.
