OL,6,FThe judge added: "I do not accept it
OL,7,Fis a technical breach."Indeed, as the
OL,8,Fdeputy leader of the council, a
OL,9,Fposition of some significance, it
OL,10,Fmight be thought that he was a man who
OL,11,Fmore so ought to have known of his
OL,12,Fobligations as regards disclosure of
OL,13,Fhis interests.
OL,15,F"I accept what is said ` that there is
OL,16,Fno obvious benefit by his non-
OL,17,Fdisclosure.
OL,19,F"It cannot be suggested that, for
OL,20,Fexample, it was motivated to avoid
OL,21,Fscrutiny of his loan to his friend.
